g.aria-label: sto przedstawiane sa z punktu widzenia magistrali)w przypadku rozdzielonych linii danych i adresu: - zamiast sygna
u "Adres / Not Data" jest m-bitowa szyna adresowa - dekoder adresu nie korzysta z linii danych tylko z szyny adresowej

read (RD) and write (WR) signals expressed from the point of view of the connected device: WR = write to the bus RD = read from the bus (often presented from the point of view of the bus) in the case of separated data and address lines: - instead of the "Address / Not Data" signal there is an m-bit address bus - the address decoder does not use the data line but the address bus
